      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, i need help writing a rejection email for a candidate. They made it to the final round for a senior dev role here in Austin, so it's a tough one. They were really strong in system design and had great culture fit, but we just went with someone who had a bit more experience with our specific cloud stack. Can you draft something professional and kind so we don't burn a bridge?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can help you draft a rejection email that's both professional and kind. Here's a sample:\n\n\"Dear [Candidate Name],\n\nI wanted to personally reach out and express our gratitude for the time and effort you invested in our company during the final round of interviews for the Senior Developer position. Your passion for system design and commitment to our company culture truly impressed us, and we appreciate the enthusiasm you brought to the table.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience with our specific cloud stack aligns more closely with our current needs. Please know that this decision was not made lightly, and we were genuinely impressed by your skills and fit with our team.\n\nWe appreciate your interest in our company and wish you the best of luck in your ongoing job search. We hope to have the opportunity to work with you again in the future.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\"\n\nThis email aims to acknowledge the candidate's strengths, express appreciation for their interest, and provide a clear explanation for the decision. Remember to keep it professional and kind, as you want to maintain a positive relationship with the candidate.",
