      "content": "Here's an updated version:\n\n\"Dear [Candidate Name],\n\nI wanted to personally reach out and express our gratitude for the time and effort you invested in our company during the final round of interviews for the Senior Developer position. Your passion for system design and commitment to our company culture truly impressed us, and we appreciate the enthusiasm you brought to the table.\n\nWe were particularly impressed by your unique blend of technical expertise and cultural fit, and we were excited to see how you would contribute to our team's dynamic. Although we ultimately decided to move forward with another candidate, we want you to know that this decision was in no way a reflection on your qualifications or potential. The competition for this role was fierce, and we were blown away by the caliber of candidates we received.\n\nWe appreciate your interest in our company and wish you the best of luck in your ongoing job search. We hope to have the opportunity to work with you again in the future.\n\nBest regards,\n[Your Name]\"\n\nI added a sentence to acknowledge the competitiveness of the process and to let the candidate know that their qualifications were not in question. This should help to convey that you valued their time and effort, and that the decision was not a quick dismissal.",
